<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="1602" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="26.[143,1104,949,1197]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602">
The species has been reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[547,660,949,973]" name="Colombia" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[715,830,949,973]" name="Argentina" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf ZP" box="[844,1010,949,973]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602" pagination="1 - 585" refId="ref12831" refString="Metcalf ZP. 1963 a. General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 1. Cicadidae. Section I. Tibiceninae. NC St Coll Contr. 1502: 1 - 585." type="journal article" year="1963">Metcalf 1963a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Duffels JP &amp; van der Laan PA" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602" refId="ref12245" refString="Duffels JP, van der Laan PA. 1985. Catalogue of the Cicadoidea (Homoptera, Auchenorhyncha) 1956 - 1980. Series Entomologica 34. Dordrect: Dr. W. Junk Publishers." type="journal volume" year="1985">Duffels and van der Laan 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn AF &amp; Heath JE &amp; Heath MS &amp; Noriega FG" box="[429,671,981,1005]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602" pagination="319 - 328" refId="ref13419" refString="Sanborn AF, Heath JE, Heath MS, Noriega FG. 1995 a. Thermoregulation by endogenous heat production in two South American grass dwelling cicadas (Homoptera: Cicadidae: Proarna). Fla Entomol. 78: 319 - 328." type="journal article" year="1995">Sanborn et al. 1995a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="De Santis &amp; CL &amp; Medrano MC &amp; Sanborn AF &amp; Bolcatto PG" box="[684,929,981,1005]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602" pagination="1 - 19" refId="ref11815" refString="De Santis CL, Medrano MC, Sanborn AF, Bolcatto PG. 2007. Cicadidos (Insecta: Hemiptera: Cicadidae) del Museo Provincial de Ciencias Naturales &quot; Florentino Ameghino &quot; Santa Fe, Argentina. Mus Prov Cien Nat &quot; Florentino Ameghino &quot; Ser Cat. No. 19: 1 - 19." type="book chapter" year="2007">De Santis et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
). However, the species was mistakenly listed as occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[644,757,1013,1037]" name="Colombia" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602">Colombia</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf ZP" box="[797,979,1013,1037]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602" pagination="1 - 585" refId="ref12831" refString="Metcalf ZP. 1963 a. General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 1. Cicadidae. Section I. Tibiceninae. NC St Coll Contr. 1502: 1 - 585." type="journal article" year="1963">Metcalf (1963a)</bibRefCitation>
. The paper by 
<bibRefCitation author="Distant WL" box="[178,341,1045,1069]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602" pagination="54 - 67" refId="ref11979" refString="Distant WL. 1892. On some undescribed Cicadidae, with synonymical notes. Ann Mag Nat Hist. (6) 10: 54 - 67." type="journal article" year="1892">Distant (1892)</bibRefCitation>
lists only 
<collectingCountry box="[454,609,1045,1069]" name="Argentina" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602">the Argentine</collectingCountry>
Republic as the source of specimens for the new species. The listing of 
<collectingCountry box="[447,560,1077,1101]" name="Colombia" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602">Colombia</collectingCountry>
appears to be the result of misreading the table and assigning 
<collectingCountry box="[304,417,1109,1133]" name="Colombia" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602">Colombia</collectingCountry>
as a location for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[613,701,1109,1133]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tympanoterpes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bergi">
<emphasis box="[613,701,1109,1133]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602">P. bergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
when in actuality it refers to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1892" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Ariasa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombiae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602">Ariasa colombiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. All other records for the species are currently from 
<collectingCountry box="[847,965,1141,1165]" name="Argentina" pageId="26" pageNumber="1602">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. As a result, the species is removed from the Colombian cicada fauna.
</paragraph>
